		"name": "Messaging App API",
		"description": "# Messaging App API\n\nThe Messaging App API is a RESTful backend service built using Django REST Framework and JWT authentication. It enables secure one-on-one conversations between registered users, allowing them to create conversations, and messages, retrieve message history, and manage access through authentication and permissions.\n\nThis API powers the core messaging features of the application, ensuring users can exchange messages reliably while maintaining privacy and secure access to their data.\n\n## Core Features\n\n### Authentication (JWT)\n\n- Register new users\n    \n- Login to obtain access + refresh token\n    \n- Refresh expired tokens\n    \n- Protect private endpoints with Bearer Tokens\n    \n\n### Conversations\n\n- Create a converation with one or multiple participants\n    \n- Retrieve a list of conversations belonging to the authenticated user\n    \n- Fetch all messages within a specific conversation\n    \n- Delete conversations owned by the user\n    \n\n### Messages\n\n- Send messages inside a conversation\n    \n- Retrieve paginated messages (20 per page or customizable via query params)\n    \n- Filter messages by:\n    \n    - sender\n        \n    - sent_after\n        \n    - sent_before\n        \n\n### Filtering & Pagination\n\n- Powered by django-filters\n    \n- Custom pagination for messages\n    \n- Query string filtering such as:\n    \n\n``` ruby\n?page=2\n&page_size=10\n?sender=5\n?start_date=2025-10-01&end_date=2025-11-01\n\n ```\n\n## Permissions & Access Control\n\nThe API enforces strict privacy rules:\n\n- Users can access only their own conversations\n    \n- A user cannot read or modify another user's messages\n    \n- Only authenticated users can send or view messages\n    \n- Custom permission classes ensure message and conversation ownership\n    \n\n## API Technology Stack\n\n- Django 5+\n    \n- Django REST Framework\n    \n- SimpleJWT\n    \n- django-filter\n    \n- mysqlclient\n    \n- drf-yasg\n    \n- django-extensions\n    \n\n## Testing (Postman)\n\nThe API is fully testable via Postman:\n\n- Collections include:\n    \n    - Authentication\n        \n    - Conversations\n        \n    - Messages\n        \n    - Unauthorized Operations\n        \n        - Conversations\n            \n        - Messages\n            \n    - Collection variables store `access_token` , `user_1` `user_2` `user_3` `conversation_id` and `message_id`\n        \n    - Token-based authentication via `Authentication: Bearer`\n        \n\n## Use Cases\n\n- Real-time chat applications\n    \n- Support message systems\n    \n- Internal messaging for business platforms\n    \n- Social networking apps\n    \n- Learning platforms with messaging features\n    \n\n## Summary\n\nThis messaging App API provides a secure and scalable foundation for user-to-user communication. With powerful filtering, robust authentication, and strict permission control, it ensures a safe and efficient messaging experience sutiable for modern applications.",
